1
00:00:02,628 --> 00:00:04,078
Today was fun.

2
00:00:04,730 --> 00:00:06,780
Really.

3
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,060
Just fun?

4
00:00:12,230 --> 00:00:13,230
Hm?

5
00:00:14,406 --> 00:00:18,516
Kakeru, what do you think about Koharu?

6
00:00:20,310 --> 00:00:21,310
Huh?

7
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:25,170
Do you like Koharu?

8
00:00:33,580 --> 00:00:35,160
What are you saying?

9
00:00:39,415 --> 00:00:41,900
Hurry up and answer!

10
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:43,340
You were listening?

11
00:00:43,340 --> 00:00:44,870
I came back for my wallet.

12
00:00:44,870 --> 00:00:47,645
I was at the door
for what felt like eternity.

13
00:00:47,645 --> 00:00:49,385
Who cares?

14
00:00:55,510 --> 00:00:56,890
Kakeru.

15
00:00:58,580 --> 00:01:01,520
In manga, movies, and TV dramas,
it's always the same.

16
00:01:02,445 --> 00:01:06,700
When someone asks if you like them,
if you can't answer right away,

17
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:07,940
then you do.

18
00:01:09,745 --> 00:01:11,380
Huh?

19
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:14,610
Love, like the flying trapeze,
is all about timing.

20
00:01:16,090 --> 00:01:18,080
You might lose your chance.

21
00:01:21,650 --> 00:01:23,200
Stop messing around.

22
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:53,610
Many people still reach full recovery.

23
00:01:54,505 --> 00:01:58,500
Please don't give up.

24
00:01:58,500 --> 00:02:01,370
In that moment, I thought,

25
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:08,010
"Ah, maybe he could be..."

26
00:02:10,210 --> 00:02:11,960
But maybe it's impossible...

27
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,390
for someone like me.

28
00:02:20,495 --> 00:02:21,930
Thank you very much.

29
00:02:21,930 --> 00:02:23,535
Koharu.

30
00:02:23,535 --> 00:02:24,915
Good job.

31
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,500
Let's go.

32
00:02:38,605 --> 00:02:41,060
I just had a checkup the other day.

33
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:42,530
It's so soon, isn't it?

34
00:02:49,510 --> 00:02:50,830
Mom?

35
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:53,920
Hey, do you remember?

36
00:02:54,980 --> 00:02:57,140
When you first lost your sight.

37
00:02:58,762 --> 00:03:03,412
I put all the vases away
because I thought it was dangerous, right?

38
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:05,930
Oh, yeah.

39
00:03:06,603 --> 00:03:10,473
Then, you said that
all the colors disappeared.

40
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:14,230
That the scents were gone.

41
00:03:15,050 --> 00:03:17,930
Even if you'd get hurt,
you wanted the flowers.

42
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:20,990
Did I say that?

43
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:27,620
I don't know who this person you like is.

44
00:03:29,630 --> 00:03:31,870
But if you keep hiding those feelings,

45
00:03:32,963 --> 00:03:34,316
won't all the colors...

46
00:03:35,513 --> 00:03:36,903
fade away again?

47
00:03:58,160 --> 00:03:59,480
Koharu.

48
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,710
Good morning.

49
00:04:04,510 --> 00:04:05,800
It's Kakeru.

50
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:17,790
Good morning.

51
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:20,520
Morning.

52
00:05:08,115 --> 00:05:11,110
[Episode 3]

53
00:05:11,110 --> 00:05:12,520
Kakeru?

54
00:05:13,890 --> 00:05:14,890
Hm?

55
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:18,740
Phew, you're still here.

56
00:05:19,405 --> 00:05:21,630
Sorry, I was hiding my presence.

57
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:22,995
Don't do that, okay?

58
00:05:22,995 --> 00:05:24,385
Sorry, sorry.

59
00:05:26,935 --> 00:05:30,870
Thanks for the other day.

60
00:05:30,870 --> 00:05:33,170
For taking me shopping.

61
00:05:34,095 --> 00:05:36,960
I enjoyed it. It was a new experience.

62
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:39,040
I've never gone on my own.

63
00:05:44,335 --> 00:05:46,720
I was thinking about
that guy from the café.

64
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,270
Oh, the one on the phone.

65
00:05:49,270 --> 00:05:51,430
Think about the natto's feelings!

66
00:05:51,430 --> 00:05:53,705
What kind of conversation was that?

67
00:05:53,705 --> 00:05:56,785
That was hilarious.

68
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:02,860
- Um...
- When should we set off the fireworks?

69
00:06:03,895 --> 00:06:04,920
Huh?

70
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Hm?

71
00:06:08,780 --> 00:06:11,530
I was just about to say the same thing.

72
00:06:25,430 --> 00:06:28,630
- The two of us could...
- How about inviting everyone?

73
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,640
Huh?

74
00:06:31,630 --> 00:06:33,665
We have plenty of fireworks.

75
00:06:33,665 --> 00:06:37,245
Besides, what matters
is having everyone look up, right?

76
00:06:41,403 --> 00:06:42,423
Yes.

77
00:06:45,915 --> 00:06:48,210
Oh?

78
00:06:48,210 --> 00:06:50,290
Kakeru said that?

79
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:52,775
With everyone, huh?

80
00:06:52,775 --> 00:06:54,750
So what?

81
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:56,805
You don't like fireworks?

82
00:06:56,805 --> 00:07:00,245
No, I absolutely love fireworks.

83
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,500
It's just…

84
00:07:08,755 --> 00:07:11,970
Well, never mind.
Then let's go set off some fireworks.

85
00:07:12,685 --> 00:07:14,410
Thank you!

86
00:07:14,410 --> 00:07:16,120
Where should we do it?

87
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:18,990
The park on the other side
of the station should work.

88
00:07:18,990 --> 00:07:22,660
All right. Then Kakeru,
grab the fireworks and a bucket.

89
00:07:22,660 --> 00:07:24,430
Yuuko, food and drinks.

90
00:07:24,430 --> 00:07:25,680
I'll bring a lighter.

91
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,790
And Koharu, bring your excitement.

92
00:07:27,790 --> 00:07:29,985
Wait, just a lighter?

93
00:07:29,985 --> 00:07:32,175
That's not fair.

94
00:07:32,175 --> 00:07:34,080
Don't you get it?

95
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:36,676
The lighting of fireworks,
by the lighter, for the lighter...

96
00:07:36,676 --> 00:07:38,786
You just like the word "lighter."

97
00:07:40,130 --> 00:07:42,220
Kakeru…

98
00:07:42,915 --> 00:07:45,310
Kakeru!

99
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:47,190
Oh, sorry, what?

100
00:07:47,190 --> 00:07:49,605
You really are something else.

101
00:07:49,605 --> 00:07:51,495
Just forget it.

102
00:07:54,495 --> 00:07:58,300
Are you sure about just being good friends?

103
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:00,180
You're still hung up on that?

104
00:08:05,290 --> 00:08:06,640
Look.

105
00:08:07,580 --> 00:08:10,480
Taking the first step
is terrifying for everyone.

106
00:08:16,005 --> 00:08:20,040
But without that step,

107
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:22,110
she'll never know how you feel.

108
00:08:57,710 --> 00:08:59,110
You're early.

109
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:02,700
I wanted to get everything ready.

110
00:09:04,445 --> 00:09:06,570
You actually brought stuff.

111
00:09:06,570 --> 00:09:09,590
Because that guy
might actually only bring a lighter.

112
00:09:13,255 --> 00:09:15,010
You never know.

113
00:09:15,010 --> 00:09:17,770
Wow, zero faith in him.

114
00:09:18,815 --> 00:09:21,410
Speaking of fireworks...

115
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:23,260
Remember that incident?

116
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,520
When my sandals burned?

117
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:29,770
You screamed running around the riverbank.

118
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:31,100
That was a disaster.

119
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:33,751
You and Haruto didn't help me at all.

120
00:09:33,751 --> 00:09:35,441
I said sorry.

121
00:09:46,594 --> 00:09:47,640
Hm?

122
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:51,070
Oh. It's nothing.

123
00:10:01,590 --> 00:10:02,990
Koharu.

124
00:10:06,065 --> 00:10:09,460
I'm sorry. I'm late.

125
00:10:12,295 --> 00:10:14,720
What an amazing yukata!

126
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:18,415
I always wanted to do fireworks,
so I got excited.

127
00:10:18,415 --> 00:10:21,005
So cute! It suits you so well.

128
00:10:21,005 --> 00:10:22,005
Right?

129
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:26,930
- It's really elegant.
- That's your response?

130
00:10:28,390 --> 00:10:29,790
Thanks.

131
00:10:31,305 --> 00:10:33,070
Thank you very much.

132
00:10:33,070 --> 00:10:35,090
- Mrs. Fuyutsuki.
- Yuuko.

133
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,880
I'm Kakeru.

134
00:10:40,450 --> 00:10:42,850
We take classes together.

135
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:46,740
Ah.

136
00:10:48,495 --> 00:10:50,420
Thank you for your help.

137
00:10:50,420 --> 00:10:52,690
No, it's my pleasure.

138
00:11:02,330 --> 00:11:03,620
Mom?

139
00:11:04,373 --> 00:11:07,380
Well, I'll be heading off now.

140
00:11:07,380 --> 00:11:09,385
- Have fun, okay?
- Okay.

141
00:11:13,245 --> 00:11:15,580
All right, let's go.

142
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:16,620
Okay.

143
00:11:19,085 --> 00:11:21,330
Ushio? What are you doing?

144
00:11:21,330 --> 00:11:23,085
Everyone's here.

145
00:11:23,085 --> 00:11:25,185
<i>I got lost.</i>

146
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,240
Huh?

147
00:11:28,035 --> 00:11:32,090
So that's this road here...

148
00:11:32,090 --> 00:11:34,145
- Here?
- Yeah.

149
00:11:34,825 --> 00:11:37,650
So, since that's here,

150
00:11:37,650 --> 00:11:39,620
go straight to the end of the road.

151
00:11:39,620 --> 00:11:42,910
- Okay.
- Then just turn right at the end.

152
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:44,720
- Straight, then right.
- Yes!

153
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,914
Okay, thank you!

154
00:11:45,914 --> 00:11:47,689
- Take care!
- Thanks.

155
00:11:49,755 --> 00:11:52,210
You weren't lost at all!

156
00:11:52,210 --> 00:11:55,345
I thought I'd give Kakeru and Koharu
some alone time.

157
00:11:55,345 --> 00:11:57,205
Pretty genius idea, right?

158
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,020
Yuuko?

159
00:12:02,945 --> 00:12:04,650
Impressive.

160
00:12:04,650 --> 00:12:05,790
Right?

161
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:11,395
Then, we have the Purple Peony.

162
00:12:13,375 --> 00:12:16,260
The one that blooms
like a peony in the sky, right?

163
00:12:16,260 --> 00:12:17,705
You remembered?

164
00:12:17,705 --> 00:12:19,075
Of course!

165
00:12:24,430 --> 00:12:28,700
<i>Sorry! Something urgent came up,
so Yuuko and I can't make it!</i>

166
00:12:29,690 --> 00:12:31,580
Something urgent?

167
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:37,250
That guy…

168
00:12:38,195 --> 00:12:40,450
Is something wrong?

169
00:12:40,450 --> 00:12:43,220
No, it's nothing.

170
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:47,680
And finally, Umbrella Blizzard.

171
00:12:48,899 --> 00:12:51,726
The one where parachutes
come drifting down.

172
00:12:51,726 --> 00:12:55,256
Yeah, I thought
it'd be perfect for the finale.

173
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,650
Plus...

174
00:12:59,915 --> 00:13:02,567
if you can touch a parachute,

175
00:13:02,567 --> 00:13:06,967
you can feel the fireworks,
not just hear them.

176
00:13:08,450 --> 00:13:12,200
There are about twenty of them,
so you might catch at least one.

177
00:13:13,555 --> 00:13:16,180
We can do it like a watermelon-smashing game,

178
00:13:16,180 --> 00:13:18,260
yelling out "right" and "left."

179
00:13:23,190 --> 00:13:24,460
Then...

180
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:28,870
if I manage to catch even one…

181
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:33,350
Can I ask you for something?

182
00:13:35,510 --> 00:13:36,510
Huh?

183
00:13:39,450 --> 00:13:41,390
Will you grant my wish?

184
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:46,550
Sure.

185
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:54,930
Rain.

186
00:13:57,020 --> 00:13:58,570
Come over here!

187
00:14:11,070 --> 00:14:14,320
I was so happy.

188
00:14:14,320 --> 00:14:17,530
Kakeru used to be like damp concrete.

189
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:22,030
But after meeting Koharu,
he's like a warm, cozy blanket.

190
00:14:22,030 --> 00:14:25,155
Hey, shouldn't we head back after all?

191
00:14:25,155 --> 00:14:26,880
Why?

192
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:29,680
Kakeru's not very reliable, you know.

193
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:32,880
He can be pretty clueless.
I'm worried about Koharu.

194
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:36,570
It's fine. It's not just for show.
He actually helps her out.

195
00:14:36,570 --> 00:14:39,040
It's starting to rain now.

196
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,660
- Such bad luck.
- Yeah, really.

197
00:14:40,660 --> 00:14:42,600
- Rain?
- Do you have a towel?

198
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:43,950
Maybe...

199
00:14:43,950 --> 00:14:45,460
It's fine.

200
00:14:45,460 --> 00:14:49,245
He's been studying up
with his care giving books.

201
00:14:49,245 --> 00:14:52,115
That's how much he cares.

202
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:55,030
Though he hasn't realized it.

203
00:15:09,770 --> 00:15:10,820
Um...

204
00:15:12,020 --> 00:15:14,620
Here, you can use this.

205
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,580
Sorry.

206
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:20,400
No, it's not that.

207
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:22,860
Um...

208
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:29,340
Do my eyes look like a panda's?

209
00:15:37,970 --> 00:15:39,310
Kakeru?

210
00:15:40,950 --> 00:15:41,950
Oh.

211
00:15:43,116 --> 00:15:44,876
Sorry, my presence.

212
00:15:47,130 --> 00:15:48,600
I can still sense you...

213
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:51,930
at this distance.

214
00:16:09,460 --> 00:16:12,690
The rain's letting up.

215
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,760
You're right.

216
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:20,240
Thank goodness.

217
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:22,970
We can set off fireworks.

218
00:16:37,675 --> 00:16:39,290
It's stopped, so it should be fine.

219
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:41,895
I'm still worried. Sorry.

220
00:16:41,895 --> 00:16:43,315
Let's drink another time.

221
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,080
What's wrong?

222
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:56,180
You...

223
00:16:57,410 --> 00:16:58,960
Don't tell me...

224
00:17:05,765 --> 00:17:07,500
Sorry.

225
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:11,635
If I'd gathered everything sooner,
they'd all be safe.

226
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:17,920
The sparklers still survived though, right?

227
00:17:19,290 --> 00:17:20,700
Yeah, but...

228
00:17:22,008 --> 00:17:27,133
Yuuko and Ushio couldn't make it,
but it turned out for the best.

229
00:17:27,133 --> 00:17:28,993
They didn't get wet.

230
00:17:31,705 --> 00:17:34,050
Let's try again another time.

231
00:17:34,050 --> 00:17:37,010
Ushio said he loves fireworks too,

232
00:17:39,046 --> 00:17:40,976
so it'll definitely be fun.

233
00:17:43,350 --> 00:17:44,460
Yeah.

234
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:48,510
Honestly,

235
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:53,020
I had something I wanted to tell you.

236
00:17:54,665 --> 00:17:57,430
But I was scared,

237
00:17:57,430 --> 00:18:00,120
so I thought
I'd borrow the fireworks' strength.

238
00:18:01,857 --> 00:18:06,960
But I guess the heavens
are telling me it's not time yet.

239
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:12,800
Then...

240
00:18:15,510 --> 00:18:18,960
can I use that strength
from the fireworks instead?

241
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:21,460
Huh?

242
00:18:39,350 --> 00:18:40,820
This is…

243
00:18:42,070 --> 00:18:43,470
A parachute.

244
00:18:44,815 --> 00:18:48,870
It got wet, so I reached in
and pulled it out.

245
00:18:54,620 --> 00:18:58,130
Will you listen to my request?

246
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,360
Yes.

247
00:19:10,130 --> 00:19:12,310
Stop forcing yourself to smile.

248
00:19:14,730 --> 00:19:15,730
Huh?

249
00:19:16,725 --> 00:19:19,220
You waited a long time for this.

250
00:19:19,220 --> 00:19:21,211
You must be disappointed.

251
00:19:21,211 --> 00:19:25,261
If that's the case, just frown properly.

252
00:19:28,730 --> 00:19:33,090
You don't have to hide your feelings.

253
00:19:41,510 --> 00:19:44,510
What about you, Kakeru?

254
00:19:45,210 --> 00:19:46,230
Hm?

255
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:51,390
What kind of face are you making right now?

256
00:19:55,190 --> 00:19:57,720
A terrifying frown.

257
00:19:59,365 --> 00:20:00,640
Really?

258
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:01,990
Really, really.

259
00:20:03,036 --> 00:20:08,580
There's a way to know someone's face
even if I can't see.

260
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:09,680
Huh?

261
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:14,820
I go like this...

262
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:17,500
and touch your face.

263
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,510
Is that okay?

264
00:20:29,740 --> 00:20:30,800
Yeah.

265
00:20:49,170 --> 00:20:52,040
You're not frowning at all.

266
00:21:34,810 --> 00:21:36,460
Good night.

267
00:21:49,270 --> 00:21:51,180
<i>The first step…</i>

268
00:22:02,353 --> 00:22:04,003
<i>is scary for everyone.</i>

269
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:13,580
<i>But at this moment, surely,</i>

270
00:22:17,890 --> 00:22:19,750
<i>I should have taken it.</i>

271
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:36,890
<i>Before she's out of my reach.</i>

272
00:22:43,690 --> 00:22:46,360
<i>Message from Kakeru.</i>

273
00:22:54,670 --> 00:22:57,040
<i>Thanks for today. See you tomorrow.</i>

274
00:23:00,490 --> 00:23:02,260
See you tomorrow.

275
00:23:28,586 --> 00:23:30,021
Koharu?

276
00:23:30,021 --> 00:23:34,586
Koharu!

277
00:23:36,945 --> 00:23:41,760
Koharu!

278
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:45,600
Hang in there! Koharu!

279
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:49,110
When you didn't come on time,
I thought something happened.

280
00:23:49,110 --> 00:23:50,200
I found Koharu!

281
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,560
She's at Aoba Hospital.

282
